<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-412-276  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 412 276.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Robotics Today  Fall 1989 v2 n3 p2(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Robots shine in electric industry.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Roman, Harry T.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Rising operating and maintenance costs, stringent safetyregulations and high system reliability in electric utilities andnuclear power plants is increasing the potential for robotapplications.andP;  Robot devices can save an electric utility between$10,000 and $100,000 a year.andP;  The applications being considered innuclear power plants include primary containment inspection,reactor maintenance, routine health physics tests, operation andmaintenance procedures, facility decontamination anddecommissioning, and post-accident recovery.andP;  Applications alsoextend into fossil-fired plants where hazardous, monotonous andrepetitive tasks could be performed by robotic devices.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     RobotsUtilitiesNuclear Power PlantsTrends.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Potential robot applications. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>